abilities and those skills taught in the course of learning how to paint. They focus their discussion on a group of painting masters loosely associated with the prestigious Kano painting atelier, Japan's de facto painting academy throughout the Tokugawa period (1615-1868) and into the early modern era. By delving into why, how, and what these painters transmitted to students through their teaching, readers gain insight into artistic and aesthetic sensibilities active in Japanese painting and a fuller appreciation of extant paintings within their cultural and historical contexts.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aKanō School. 0aKanō School. 0aPaintingxStudy and teachingzJapanxHistory. 0aPainting, JapaneseyEdo period, 1600-1868. 7aART / Asian / General.2bisacsh1 aChance, Frank, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGerhart, Karen M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJordan, Brenda G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJordan, Brenda G., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMcclintock, Martha J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRimer, J . Thomas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWeston, Victoria, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWeston, Victoria, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAsian Studies Backlist (2000-2014) eBook Packagez978311064977208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUHP eBook Package 2000-2013z978311056414308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Hawaii Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2015z978311066325940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978082486200840uhttps://www.